---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="How to Submit an ARB Request" description="Step-by-step guide to submitting an architectural review request through the Member Portal. Easy to follow for everyone.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-20">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-heading font-bold text-clr-green mb-4">How to Submit an ARB Request</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-700 font-body text-lg">
        This guide walks you through submitting an architectural review request online. You can work at your own pace and save your progress.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4">
        <a href="/portal/login" class="text-clr-orange font-semibold hover:underline">Sign in to the Member Portal</a> to get started, or read the steps below first.
      </p>
    </div>

    <nav class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-4 mb-10" aria-label="On this page">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-2">On this page</p>
      <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
        <li><a href="#step1" class="text-clr-green hover:underline">1. Sign in</a></li>
        <li><a href="#step2" class="text-clr-green hover:underline">2. Start a new request</a></li>
        <li><a href="#step3" class="text-clr-green hover:underline">3. Fill out the form and add attachments</a></li>
        <li><a href="#step4" class="text-clr-green hover:underline">4. Save or submit</a></li>
        <li><a href="#step5" class="text-clr-green hover:underline">5. After you submit</a></li>
        <li><a href="#editing" class="text-clr-green hover:underline">Editing or revising a request</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>

    <div class="space-y-10">
      <section id="step1" class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-clr-green text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-heading font-bold text-lg">1</div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-clr-green mb-2">Sign in to the Member Portal</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-body mb-2">
              Go to the <a href="/portal/login" class="text-clr-orange font-semibold hover:underline">Member Portal</a> and sign in with the email address the HOA has on file. If you have not used the portal before, use the same email where you receive HOA notices.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="step2" class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-clr-green text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-heading font-bold text-lg">2</div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-clr-green mb-2">Start a new request</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-body mb-2">
              From the portal menu, click <strong>New ARB request</strong>. You will see a form with fields for your name, phone, property address, type of application (e.g. Exterior Paint, Fencing), and a description of your project.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-body text-sm">
              Have your information ready: property address, a clear description of what you want to do, and any photos, plans, or documents (images or PDFs). You can add attachments in the next step.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="step3" class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-clr-green text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-heading font-bold text-lg">3</div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-clr-green mb-2">Fill out the form and add attachments</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-body mb-2">
              Complete every field that applies. The <strong>Description of changes</strong> field is required. Be as specific as you can so the ARB can review your request without delay.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-body mb-2">
              Use the <strong>Attachments</strong> section to upload photos, site plans, color samples, or PDFs. You can upload multiple files. Each file can be up to 5 MB; the total for one request is 25 MB. Accepted types: images (JPEG, PNG, GIF, WebP, HEIC) and PDF.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-body text-sm">
              You do not have to finish in one sitting. You can save and come back later (see Step 4).
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="step4" class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-clr-green text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-heading font-bold text-lg">4</div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-clr-green mb-2">Save or submit</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-body mb-2">
              When you are done filling out the form and adding attachments, you have two choices:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 font-body space-y-2 mb-4">
              <li><strong>Save</strong> – Saves your work and keeps the request in draft. You can come back later to add more or make changes. The ARB does not see the request until you submit it for review.</li>
              <li><strong>Save and submit</strong> – Saves your work and sends the request to the ARB for review in one step. Use this when you are ready for the ARB to look at it.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-body mb-2">
              If you started a request earlier and left it as a draft, go to <strong>My requests</strong> in the portal. Open your request and click <strong>Edit this request</strong>. You will see the same two options: <strong>Save</strong> (just save changes) or <strong>Save and submit</strong> (save and send to the ARB).
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-body text-sm">
              Before the request goes to the ARB, you must check the box to confirm your electronic signature. Do not start work until you receive an approval.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="step5" class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-clr-green text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-heading font-bold text-lg">5</div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-clr-green mb-2">After you submit</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-body mb-2">
              Your request will show as <strong>In review</strong> on the My requests page. The ARB will look at it and may:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 font-body space-y-1 mb-4">
              <li><strong>Approve</strong> – You will see an approval notice with the date and the ARB member who approved it. You can then proceed (subject to any other permits or rules).</li>
              <li><strong>Reject</strong> – You will see a rejection with the date and ARB member. You can copy the request to start a new one with changes if you wish.</li>
              <li><strong>Request revision</strong> – The ARB will send the request back to you with a note explaining what is needed (e.g. "Please add a site survey" or "Paint color samples needed"). You can edit the request and submit it again.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-body text-sm">
              You can print or save any request as a PDF from My requests for your records.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="editing" class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-clr-green mb-4">Editing or revising a request</h2>
        <ul class="text-gray-700 font-body space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Draft (pending)</strong> – You can edit the request anytime. Use <strong>Save</strong> to keep changes, or <strong>Save and submit</strong> when you are ready to send it to the ARB. You can also cancel the request if you no longer need it.</li>
          <li><strong>In review</strong> – The ARB is reviewing it. You cannot edit until they either approve, reject, or send it back for revision.</li>
          <li><strong>Revision requested</strong> – The ARB sent it back with notes. Open the request and you will see their notes at the top. Edit the request to address the notes, then use <strong>Save and submit</strong> to send it back to the ARB.</li>
          <li><strong>Approved or rejected</strong> – The request is complete. You can copy it to start a new request with similar details if you want to apply again (e.g. after a rejection).</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200 text-center">
      <p class="text-gray-600 font-body mb-4">Ready to submit?</p>
      <a href="/portal/login" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-clr-green hover:brightness-110 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-xl font-semibold text-sm shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl transition-all">
        Sign in to Member Portal
      </a>
      <p class="mt-6 text-sm text-gray-500">
        For more on what the ARB reviews and community standards, see the <a href="/arb-process" class="text-clr-orange hover:underline">ARB Process Guide</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
